{"id":15,"parent_id":0,"book_id":44,"content_id":1,"language_id":1,"display_order":15,"title":"Lesson 14: The Law of Consecration","subtitle":"","short_title":"Lesson 14","uri":"/manual/doctrine-and-covenants-and-church-history-class-member-study-guide/lesson-14-the-law-of-consecration","content":[["div",{"id":"head1","uri":"/manual/doctrine-and-covenants-and-church-history-class-member-study-guide/lesson-14-the-law-of-consecration.head1"},[".titleNumber","Lesson",["span.dominant","14"]],["h1","The Law of Consecration"],[".kicker","Reading assignment:",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/42.30-42"},"Doctrine and Covenants 42:30–42"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/51"},"51"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/78"},"78"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/82"},"82"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/104.11-18"},"104:11–18"],";",["span.emphasis","Our Heritage,"],["a.crossRef",{"href":"/manual/our-heritage-a-brief-history-of-the-church-of-jesus-christ-of-latter-day-saints/chapter-three-building-the-kingdom-in-kirtland-ohio.p1"},"page 26"],"."]],[".bodyBlock",["div",{"id":"p4","uri":"/manual/doctrine-and-covenants-and-church-history-class-member-study-guide/lesson-14-the-law-of-consecration.p4"},"In February 1831, soon after the Saints began to gather in Kirtland, Ohio, the Lord revealed that they should begin to live the law of consecration. To",["span.emphasis","consecrate"],"means to set apart or dedicate something to the Lord’s service."],["ul.bullet",["li",["span.label","•"],[".para","What are the purposes of the law of consecration? (See",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/42.30-35,40,42"},"D&C 42:30–35, 40, 42"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/51.9"},"51:9"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/78.3-7,14"},"78:3–7, 14"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/82.17-19"},"82:17–19"],".)"]]],["div",{"id":"p6","uri":"/manual/doctrine-and-covenants-and-church-history-class-member-study-guide/lesson-14-the-law-of-consecration.p6"},"The law of consecration is an organized way in which individuals consecrate their time, talents, and possessions to the Church to build the Lord’s kingdom and serve His children."],["ul.bullet",["li",["span.label","•"],[".para","What do you think could be some of the blessings of living in a community where people lived the law of consecration?"]],["li",["span.label","•"],[".para","As Saints of God, we must be prepared and willing to live the law of consecration in its fulness. But we do not need to wait for a future day to consecrate our lives to the Lord. In what ways can you live the law of consecration in your life today?"]]],[".topic",["h2","Scripture Chain: The Law of Consecration"],["ul.noMarker",["li",[".para",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/4-ne/1.3"},"4 Nephi 1:3"]]],["li",[".para",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/42.30"},"D&C 42:30"]]],["li",[".para",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/49.20"},"D&C 49:20"]]],["li",[".para",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/51.3"},"D&C 51:3"]]],["li",[".para",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/78.3-6"},"D&C 78:3–6"]]],["li",[".para",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/105.5"},"D&C 105:5"]]]]]]],"refs":null}
